  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The sensory innervation of the clavicle remains an area of debate. Regional nerve blocks
      aimed at relieving pre- and post-operative pain include the superficial cervical plexus
      blocks, interscalene blocks and a combined version of the above. In this case study, the
      investigators aim to describe the protocol used in a university hospital: general anaesthesia
      with interscalene brachial plexus block, followed by optional iv morphine administration in
      phase 1 recovery and oral oxycodone on the ward.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
